	(2,'Materials Laboratory Technician / 材料实验室技术员','上海市闵行区','大专以上学历','2年以上','<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n</p><p>1. Ability to learn and safely operate the following Materials Laboratory testing equipment:<br />      1) Lab Mixer<br />      2) Lab Mill<br />      3) Lab Curing Press<br />      4) Specimen Preparation Equipment <br />2. Ability to learn and execute standard Materials Laboratory test methods and procedures, including Rheology, Instron, Accelerated Aging of Specimens, Testing raw material inventory control &amp; management, etc.<br />3. Ability to learn and operate a variety of digital and analog measurement equipments, including Digital Scales, Electronic balance, Thickness gauges, Steel rules, Calipers, Durometer, etc.<br />4. Ability to learn and conduct routine calibration, maintenance and repairs of Materials Laboratory testing     equipment. <br />5. Provide accurate interpretation of customer test requests, initiate and execute testing, evaluate and report test results.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong>\r\n</p><p>1. College Diploma or higher degree in Engineering, Chemistry, Technology, Science or Mathematics.<br />2. A minimum of 2-years of materials and/or physical testing laboratory experience.<br />3.  Must be detailed oriented, self-starting, and must be able to complete laboratory work with minimal supervision.<br />4. Strong verbal and written communication skills in Chinese and English are preferred. <br />5. Ability to facilitate, foster and assure open, honest, effective communication at and between all levels in the organization.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Work Conditions:</strong>\r\n</p><p>1. Must be able to work flexible hours including daily and weekend overtime, and alternate shifts as required to complete laboratory work.<br />2. May, on occasion, be required to perform duties other than those detailed in this job description.	</p>\r\n<p><strong>岗位职责：</strong>\r\n</p><p>1.能学习并安全操作下述实验室测试设备：<br />   1）实验室密炼机<br />2）实验室开炼机<br />3）实验室硫化机<br />4）制实验样品设备<br />2. 能学习并执行标准的材料实验室测试模式和流程，包括：流变仪，拉力机，老化烘箱，管理和控制测试材料的库存等。<br />3. 能学习并操控数码及相关测量设备，包括：电子秤，电子天平，测厚仪，卡尺，硬度计等。<br />4. 能学习并完成测试设备的日常校准、维护和修理。<br />5. 正确理解客户测试要求，主动执行测试、评估和完成测试结果报告。<br />6. 完成上级交付的其他工作。</p>\r\n<p><strong>岗位要求：</strong>\r\n</p><p>1. 工程、化学、技术、数学类大专以上学历；<br />2. 2年以上材料或物理实验室测试工作经验；<br />3. 认真仔细，积极主动，诚实高效，能独立完成实验室工作；<br />4.良好的中英文读写能力，善于沟通；<br />5. 能适应加班，轮班。</p>\r\n<p><strong>工作地点：</strong>\r\n</p><p>上海市闵行区纪翟路樽轩工业园区</p>',1,'2012-04-01 09:40:11','2012-04-01 09:40:11'),
	(3,'TBR Compound Chemist/Engineer / TBR配方工程师','固铂亚太研发中心','大专以上学历','','<p><strong>Essential Duties &amp; Responsibilities<br />主要职责：</strong>\r\n<br />•	Research and develop new TBR rubber compound formulae, methods and/or processes that can improve the performance, cost and/or quality of our tires.<br />研究并开发新型卡客车胎橡胶配方，工艺流程等以促进改善轮胎性能，降低成本和提高质量<br />•	Work with production plants to develop, specify and facilitate implementation of TBR rubber compounds to meet requirements of product performance, production, and most importantly the requirements of our customers. <br />与工厂合作开发、定义和协助配方工艺的实施，以满足工厂生产要求，尤其要达到客户需求<br />•	Support on-going material applications activities by evaluating new materials in both the laboratory and production environments.<br />•	评估新型材料在实验室和工厂的适用性，以支持正在进行的材料应用项目<br />•	Evaluate and approve new raw materials used on tire rubber compound formulae.<br />评估和批准应用于橡胶配方新的原材料<br />•	Track the performance of existing suppliers and monitor the quality, consistency and process capability of the raw materials used in tire compound formulae.<br />跟踪现在合作的供应商业绩表现，监控使用于轮胎配方原材料质量，一致性和工艺流程<br />•	Coordinate with external suppliers, universities and other outside entities in the identification, research and development of new materials for TBR tire applications.<br />与外部的供应商、高校或其他机构合作开发原材料的识别、研究等<br />•	Participate, advise or lead as needed on product development, process improvement and problem solving teams that are by nature global and multi-disciplinary. <br />如有需要参加、建议或领导产品开发、流程改进和问题解决项目组<br />•	Initiate, analyze and summarize laboratory development studies on TBR rubber compound formulae.  Document investigations and plant trials in the form of detailed technical reports, presentations and management updates.<br />发起、分析和总结轮胎配方工艺的实验室研究课题。归档技术报告，演示资料和管理层更新等。</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Education and/or Experience<br />任职所需教育背景和工作经验：</strong>\r\n<br />•	College Diploma (2-3 year) or University Degree (4-year) in Chemistry, Chemical Engineering, Material Science, or related  – required<br />大专以上学历，主修化学，化工工程，材料科学及相关学科 – 必需<br />•	No Previous Compound Experience Required<br />无相关配方经验亦可</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Skills &amp; Abilities<br />所需技能：</strong>\r\n<br />•	Multi-lingual: English &amp; Mandarin with sound skills in reading, writing &amp; speaking English<br />语言技能：良好的中英文听说读写技巧<br />•	Good communication and technical documentation skills.<br />良好的沟通和文件归档技巧<br />•	Proficiency with standard PC applications including: Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Excel.<br />熟练掌握计算机基本技能：Word, PowerPoint, Excel</p>\r\n<p><strong>Working Conditions<br />工作条件</strong>\r\n<br />•	Travel will be required, including overnight stays. <br />需要出差，可能会一天以上</p>\r\n<p><strong>Contact:<br />联系信息：</strong>\r\n<br />MAD Director<br />Tim Donley<br />2416 4205<br />tmdonley@coopertire.com</p>',2,'2012-04-01 09:45:45','2012-04-01 09:45:45'),
	(4,'Tire Testing Technician','上海市','','','<p><strong>Essential Duties &amp; Responsibilities</strong>\r\n<br />•	Ability to learn and safely operate the following tire testing equipment:<br />o	Tire Test Wheel<br />o	Tire Inspection Equipment<br />o	Tire Mounting &amp; Dismounting Equipment<br />o	Tire Balancing Machine<br />o	Vehicle Lift<br />o	Pneumatic Tools<br />o	Tire Sectioning &amp; Specimen Preparation Equipment (Saw &amp; Buffers)<br />o	Foot Print Pressure Equipment <br />o	Plunger &amp; Bead Un-seat Equipment<br />o	Shearography<br />•	Ability to learn and execute standard tire test methods and procedures, including<br />o	Cut Tire Analysis (CTA)<br />o	Accelerated Aging of Tires – Oxygen, Heat (Ovens) and etc…<br />o	Failure modes, mechanisms &amp; conditions<br />o	Tire Inventory Control &amp; Management<br />•	Ability to learn and operate a variety of digital and analog measurement equipment, including<br />o	Digital Scales<br />o	Non-skid gauges<br />o	Steel rules, diameters tapes, levels<br />o	Digital and analog pressure gauges<br />•	Ability to learn and conduct routine calibration, maintenance and repairs of tire testing equipment. <br />•	Provide accurate interpretation of customer test requests, initiate and execute testing, evaluate and report test results</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Skills &amp; Abilities</strong>\r\n<br />•	Must be detailed oriented, self-starting, and must be able to complete projects with minimal supervision.<br />•	Must have mechanical aptitude</p>\r\n<p><strong>Working Conditions</strong>\r\n<br />•	Must be able to work flexible hours including daily and weekend overtime as required to complete test programs.<br />•	May, on occasion, be required to perform duties other than those detailed in this job description.   	</p>',3,'2012-04-01 09:47:41','2012-04-01 09:47:41'),
	(5,'PCR Rubber Compounder','上海','College Diploma (2-3 year) or University Degree (4-year) in Chemistry','3 years at least','<p><strong>Essential Duties &amp; Responsibilities</strong> <br />• Research and develop new PCR rubber compound formulae, methods and/or processes that can improve the performance, cost and/or quality of our tires.<br />• Work with production plants to develop, specify and facilitate implementation of PCR rubber compounds to meet requirements of product performance, production, and most importantly the requirements of our customers. <br />• Support on-going material applications activities by evaluating new materials in both the laboratory and production environments.<br />• Evaluate and approve new raw materials used on tire rubber compound formulae.<br />• Track the performance of existing suppliers and monitor the quality, consistency and process capability of the raw materials used in tire compound formulae.<br />• Coordinate with external suppliers, universities and other outside entities in the identification, research and development of new materials for PCR tire applications.<br />• Participate, advise or lead as needed on product development, process improvement and problem solving teams that are by nature global and multi-disciplinary. <br />• Initiate, analyze and summarize laboratory development studies on PCR rubber compound formulae. Document investigations and plant trials in the form of detailed technical reports, presentations and management updates.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Education and/or Experience</strong> <br />• College Diploma (2-3 year) or University Degree (4-year) in Chemistry, Chemical Engineering, Material Science, or related – required<br />• Minimum of 3 - years of experience as a PCR tire rubber compounder – required<br />• Functional knowledge of PCR tire engineering and/or manufacturing processes – preferred</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Skills &amp; Abilities</strong> <br />• Multi-lingual: English &amp; Mandarin with sound skills in reading, writing &amp; speaking English<br />• Good communication and technical documentation skills.<br />• Proficiency with design of experiment methods with strong analytical and problem solving skills.<br />• Functional understanding of quality systems and concepts<br />• Must be detail oriented, self-starting, and must be able to complete projects with minimal supervision.<br />• Proficiency with standard PC applications including: Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Excel.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reporting Relationships</strong> <br />• The PCR Rubber Compounder reports directly to the Director of the Materials Applications Development Group (CTR-Asia Pacific).<br />• The PCR Rubber Compounder is the primary liaison between the Materials Applications Development Group (CTR-US) and CTR-Asia Pacific.<br />• The PCR Rubber Compounder is the primary liaison between the Materials Applications Development Group (CTR-Asia Pacific) and the CCT TBR Production Facility. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Working Conditions</strong> <br />• Work will be based out of the Asia Technical Center in Shanghai, China.<br />• This work is performed in an office environment, but will require working in production, laboratory, and warehouse facilities.<br />• Travel will be required, including overnight stays. </p>',4,'2012-04-01 09:49:56','2012-04-10 04:51:04'),
	(6,'Passenger Car Radial (PCR) Development Engineer','上海市','大专以上学历','3 years at least','<p><strong>Essential Duties &amp; Responsibilities</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Develop, specify and facilitate implementation of PCR tire engineering packages to meet requirements of production, product performance and most importantly the requirements of our customers. <br />2.	Participate, advise or lead as needed on product development, process improvement and problem solving teams that are by nature global and multi-disciplinary. <br />3.	Document investigations and plant trials in the form of detailed technical reports, presentations and management updates.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Education and/or Experience</strong>\r\n<br />1.	College Diploma (2-3 year) or University Degree (4-year) in Engineering, Mathematics, Technology, Science or Design – required<br />2.	Minimum of 3-years of relevant experience in tire engineering or in related industry – required <br />3.	Functional knowledge of tire compounding, tire design or manufacturing processes – preferred</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Skills &amp; Abilities</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Multi-lingual: English &amp; Mandarin with sound skills in reading, writing &amp; speaking English<br />2.	Good communication and technical documentation skills.<br />3.	Proficiency with design of experiment methods with strong analytical and problem solving skills.<br />4.	Functional understanding of quality systems and concepts<br />5.	Must be detail oriented, self-starting, and must be able to complete projects with minimal supervision.<br />6.	Proficiency with standard PC applications including: Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Excel, Access and Visio.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reporting Relationships</strong>\r\n<br />1.	The PCR Development Engineer reports directly to the Manager, PCR Tire Engineering Group (CTR – Asia Pacific).<br />2.	The PCR Development Engineer is the primary liaison between the Tire Applications Development Groups CTR-US, CTR-Europe and CTR-Asia Pacific.<br />3.	The PCR Development Engineer is the primary liaison between the Tire Applications Development Group (CTR – Asia Pacific) and the Asia-Pacific Production Facilities.  </p>\r\n<p><strong>Working Conditions</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Primary work location will be based out of the Asian Technical Center, located in Shanghai, China.<br />2.	This work is performed in an office environment, but will require working in production, laboratory, and warehouse facilities.<br />3.	Travel is necessary and should be expected, including overnight stays. This includes Cooper-Chengshan (Shandong) Tire Co., Ltd. in Rongcheng, China.</p>',5,'2012-04-01 09:51:33','2012-04-01 09:51:33'),
	(7,'Passenger Car Radial (PCR) OE Engineer','上海市','大专以上学历','3 years at least','<p><strong>Essential Duties &amp; Responsibilities</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Communicate and represent Cooper\'s position to OE customers. <br />2.	Work with OE Sales to support OE activities in China. <br />3.	Work closely with PCR Tire Development Engineers to understand overall service conditions and feedback on product performance, presentations and management updates.<br />4.	Competitive analysis of competitors tire performance.<br />5.	Frequent visit to each OE account to help maintain excellent working relationships.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Education and/or Experience</strong>\r\n<br />1.	College Diploma (2-3 year) or University Degree (4-year) in Auto or Rubber Engineering, Mathematics, Technology, Science or Design – required<br />2.	Minimum of 3-years of relevant experience in tire engineering or in related industry – required <br />3.	Functional knowledge of tire design or manufacturing processes – preferred<br />4.	Willingness on frequent business trip– required</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Skills &amp; Abilities</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Multi-lingual: English &amp; Mandarin with sound skills in reading, writing &amp; speaking English<br />2.	Good communication and technical documentation skills.<br />3.	Proficiency with design of experiment methods with strong analytical and problem solving skills.<br />4.	Functional understanding of quality systems and concepts<br />5.	Must be detail oriented, self-starting, and must be able to complete projects with minimal supervision.<br />6.	Proficiency with standard PC applications including: Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Excel and Project.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reporting Relationships</strong>\r\n<br />1.	The PCR OE Engineer reports directly to the Manager, PCR Tire Engineering Group (CTR – Asia Pacific).<br />2.	The PCR OE Engineer is the primary liaison between the Tire Applications Development Group (CTR – Asia Pacific) and the Asia-Pacific OE sales, Asia-Pacific Production Facilities.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Working Conditions</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Primary work location will be based out of the Asian Technical Center, located in Shanghai, China.<br />2.	This work is performed in an office environment, but will require working in production, laboratory, and warehouse facilities.<br />3.	Travel is necessary and frequent to OE customers or production facilities.</p>',6,'2012-04-01 09:52:58','2012-04-01 09:53:15'),
	(8,'Truck Bus Radial (TBR) Tire Development Engineer ','上海市','大专以上学历','3 years at least','<p><strong>Essential Duties &amp; Responsibilities</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Develop, specify and facilitate implementation of TBR tire engineering packages to meet requirements of production, product performance and most importantly the requirements of our customers. <br />2.	Participate, advise or lead as needed on product development, process improvement and problem solving teams that are by nature global and multi-disciplinary. <br />3.	Document investigations and plant trials in the form of detailed technical reports, presentations and management updates.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Education and/or Experience</strong>\r\n<br />1.	College Diploma (2-3 year) or University Degree (4-year) in Engineering, Mathematics, Technology, Science or Design – required<br />2.	Minimum of 3-years of relevant experience in tire engineering or in related industry – required<br />3.	Functional knowledge of tire compounding or tire design or manufacturing processes – preferred</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Skills &amp; Abilities</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Multi-lingual: English &amp; Mandarin with sound skills in reading, writing &amp; speaking English<br />2.	Good communication and technical documentation skills.<br />3.	Proficiency with design of experiment methods with strong analytical and problem solving skills.<br />4.	Functional understanding of quality systems and concepts<br />5.	Must be detail oriented, self-starting, and must be able to complete projects with minimal supervision.<br />6.	Proficiency with standard PC applications including: Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Excel, Access and Visio.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reporting Relationships</strong>\r\n<br />1.	The TBR Tire Development Engineer reports directly to the Manager of the TBR Tire Engineering Group (CTR – Asia Pacific).<br />2.	The TBR Tire Development Engineer is the primary liaison between the Tire Applications Development Groups CTR-US and CTR-Asia Pacific.<br />3.	The TBR Tire Development Engineer is the primary liaison between the Tire Applications Development Group (CTR – Asia Pacific) and the Asia-Pacific Production Facilities.  </p>\r\n<p><strong>Working Conditions</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Primary work location will be based out of the Asian Technical Center, located in Shanghai, China.<br />2.	This work is performed in an office environment, but will require working in production, laboratory, and warehouse facilities.<br />3.	Travel is necessary and should be expected, including overnight stays. This includes Cooper-Chengshan (Shandong) Tire Co., Ltd. in Rongcheng, China.</p>',7,'2012-04-01 09:57:03','2012-04-01 09:57:03'),
	(9,'Tire Designer','上海市','大专以上学历','3 years at least','<p><strong>Essential Duties &amp; Responsibilities</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Design tread proposals that are attractive, functional and that meet market requirements<br />2.	Design sidewall proposals that are attractive, functional and that meet market requirements<br />3.	Demonstrate proficient modeling skills in Pro/Engineer.<br />4.	Create new logos and letter styles<br />5.	Create tire renderings of prototype tread and sidewall designs using engineering and other modeling applications<br />6.	Coordinate the fabrication of 3-dimensional, physical models of prototype tread and sidewall designs, i.e. hand-cut tires and modeling machines</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Education and/or Experience</strong>\r\n<br />1.	College Diploma (2-3 year) or University Degree (4-year) in Engineering, Mathematics, Technology, Science, Design or Art – required<br />2.	Minimum of 3-years of relevant experience in tire design or in related industry – required <br />3.	Functional knowledge of tire mold design or tire engineering or manufacturing processes – preferred</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Skills &amp; Abilities</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Multi-lingual: English &amp; Mandarin with sound skills in reading, writing &amp; speaking English<br />2.	Good communication and technical documentation skills.<br />3.	Proficiency with design of experiment methods with strong analytical and problem solving skills.<br />4.	Functional understanding of quality systems and concepts<br />5.	Must be detail oriented, self-starting, and must be able to complete projects with minimal supervision.<br />6.	Proficiency with standard PC applications including: Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Excel, Access and Visio.<br />7.	Must be technically competent with Pro/Engineer and other modeling applications. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Reporting Relationships</strong>\r\n<br />1.	The Tire Designer reports directly to the Director of the Tire Applications Development Group (CTR – Asia Pacific).<br />2.	The Tire Designer is the primary liaison between the Product Design Group; CTR- US, CTR- Europe and CTR- Asia Pacific.<br />3.	The Tire Designer is the primary liaison between the Tire Applications Development Group (CTR – Asia Pacific) and the Asia-Pacific Production Facilities.  </p>\r\n<p><strong>Working Conditions</strong>\r\n<br />1.	Primary work location will be based out of the Asian Technical Center, located in Shanghai, China.<br />2.	This work is performed in an office environment, but will require working in production, laboratory, and warehouse facilities.<br />3.	Travel is necessary and should be expected, including overnight stays.</p>',8,'2012-04-01 09:58:19','2012-04-01 09:58:19'),
	(10,'精益六西格玛部门助理','上海','本科','','<p><strong>职位描述</strong> <br />负责维护和更新部门的系统数据；培训的安排；集团资料的英汉互译。</p>\r\n<p><strong>主要工作职责</strong>1. 及时维护和更新部门的有关精益六西格的实时进度数据；<br />2. 负责培训的安排：如教室，培训资料等。<br />3. 集团的相关资料的英汉互译，如集团的其他工厂精益六西格玛项目的汉译，亚太区的相关项目的英译；<br />4. 培训课程的培训资料的整理；<br />5. 培训反馈和培训需求的统计分析；<br />6. 亚太区绿带项目的进度跟踪；<br />7. 亚太区已结束项目的收益跟踪及异常时的及时反馈；<br />8. 为集团内部的可引用的项目交流提供协助。</p>\r\n<p><strong>学历和/或工作经历</strong> <br />1. 大学本科学历</p>\r\n<p><strong>技巧和能力 (执行必要工作职能所必需).</strong>1. 统计学专业毕业；<br />2. CET6；<br />3. 具有良好的沟通技巧及组织能力；<br />4. 要求良好的耐性及责任心；<br />5. 熟悉Microsoft Office 软件。</p>\r\n<p><strong>报告关系</strong>1. 向精益六西格玛部门负责人汇报。</p>\r\n<p><strong>工作条件 (描述工作环境)</strong> </p>\r\n<p>1. 需要经常出差；</p>',9,'2012-04-01 10:00:42','2012-04-10 04:57:12'),
	(11,'Supplier Quality Engineer ','上海','本科','5年以上','<p><strong>GENERAL SUMMARY (Describe the overall duties and responsibilities of the job):</strong>This position is responsible for measuring and reporting supplier performance metrics including supply risk. Ensuring problem resolution from the supply base and driving supplier development while supporting and maintaining all necessary internal related systems.</p>\r\n<p><strong>ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES (Duties required for successful job performance): </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:<br /><em><strong>Performance Metrics</strong> </em>\r\n<br />Maintain a tracking and reporting system for supplier quality performance, delivery performance, premium freight performance, and risk management<br />Maintain tracking of supplier quality and environmental certifications<br />Maintain a system to insure that the highest levels of quality and delivery performance are achieved from suppliers<br />Generates and publishes supplier performance scorecards<br /><strong><em>Problem Resolution</em> </strong>Communicate and drive resolution of supplier quality and delivery performance issues on a timely basis<br />Coordinates and supports supplier visits to our manufacturing plants related to quality and delivery performance issues<br /><strong><em>Supplier Development</em> </strong>Supports manufacturing plant efforts to improve performance by working on supplier related opportunities<br />Conducts audits of new potential sources, suppliers needing to improve quality and/or delivery performance, suppliers identified as high risk, and for effectiveness verification of supplier corrective action responses</p>\r\n<p>Conducts reviews with suppliers and assures implementation of corrective actions across supplier manufacturing locations for all issues resulting in a \"Stop Ship\" or \"Field Action\"</p>\r\n<p>Verifies supplier compliance by annual on-site assessments of \"High Impact to Quality\" supplier manufacturing locations</p>\r\n<p>Supports development of suppliers in the areas of improved quality and environmental operating systems </p>\r\n<p>Support Systems</p>\r\n<p>Tracks the need for and approves new supplier Production Part Approval Process (PPAP) packets </p>\r\n<p>Maintains the quality system documentation for Purchasing</p>\r\n<p>Supports internal quality system auditing as needed</p>\r\n<p>Supports Six Sigma Black/Green Belt projects targeted at improving supplier performance as needed</p>\r\n<p>General</p>\r\n<p>Maintains and extends strong and positive relationships with suppliers and ensures that all interactions both verbal and written are professional</p>\r\n<p>Remains aware of the latest developments and methods being used within the quality profession by attending meetings, seminars, training courses and reading technical publications</p>\r\n<p>REQUIRED EDUCATION and/or EXPERIENCE (These are the traditional minimum, or required, bona-fide occupational qualifications and other requirements of most people in this job).</p>\r\n<p>At a minimum this position requires four years at a university with at least 5 years of automotive manufacturing experience in the field of quality. Internal auditing experience is a desired attribute.</p>\r\n<p><br />REQUIRED SKILLS AND ABILITIES (Those needed to perform the essential functions of the job).</p>\r\n<p>This position interfaces with various groups at the company’s manufacturing locations and corporate departments as well as with suppliers through oral and written communications. This position requires <br />• Four year of university education<br />• At least 5 years of automotive manufacturing experience in the field of quality<br />• Excellent organizational, interpersonal and communication skills <br />• Excellent problem analysis and soliving capability who also can understand all aspects of the issue to make good decisions. <br />• Communicate in writing using the English language and being able to verbally communicate using the English language is a desired attribute.<br />• TS16949 experience is desirable<br />• Chemistry experience is desirable </p>\r\n<p><br />REQUIRED DECISION-MAKING AND ORGANIZATION IMPACT (Describe the typical types of decisions made by employees in this job and the likely impact of those decisions on the Company).</p>\r\n<p>This position makes decisions in terms of prioritizing work and resources that directly impact the efficiency and success of the Purchasing Department in meeting Company expectations. This person must be able to make decisions and recommendations based upon knowledge of the facts and issues.</p>\r\n<p><br />REPORTING RELATIONSHIPS (Indicate job titles for this job’s supervisor and direct reports).</p>\r\n<p>This position reports directly to the Purchasing Director and has no direct reports.</p>\r\n<p><br />WORKING CONDITIONS (Describe the environment within which the work is performed).</p>\r\n<p>This position is located in the Shanghai office and there are no unpleasant or hazardous working conditions. </p>',10,'2012-04-01 10:04:17','2012-04-10 03:17:58'),
	(12,'Logistic Specialist','上海','大专以上学历','3 years at least','<p><strong>Summary of Responsibilities<br />(Brief description of what the person will be doing in this job including % travel required)</strong> <br />1. Handle import operation <br />1.1Handle import tires on ocean transportation, Customs in China, inland transportation and warehouse receiving<br />1.2 Handle spare part &amp; facilities on import operation, including Customs, Commodity inspection etc. <br />1.3 Ensure Company\' Customs and Commodity inspection certification is under good condition<br /><br />2. Handle Customs &amp; Commodity operation for Trading Company domestics sales <br /><br />3. Handle POS and promotion product delivery and tracking delivery status <br />1.1ŸTracking delivery status and communicate with Marketing team in normal <br />1.2 Response any abnormal situation and take actions with 4 hours <br />1.3 Tracking receiving status of each order at customers and feedback any customers\' comments<br /><br />4. Handle warehouse receiving &amp; delivery out and make transactions in JDE. <br /><br />5. Handle sample tires export out of China <br /><br />6. Make monthly analysis report on import &amp; export delivery/cost and Finished Tires inventory status</p>\r\n<p><strong>Requirements<br />(Experience, education, skills, Success Profile traits, designations, etc.)</strong> <br /><br />1. College\'s degree and above<br />2. At least 3 years purchasing experience on import &amp; export<br />3. Good communicate in English<br />4. Good negotiation &amp; communication Skills<br />5. Familiar with ERP system <br />6. Good team player <br />7. Energetic and enthusiastic</p>',11,'2012-04-01 10:06:07','2012-04-10 04:59:28'),
	(13,'Materials Engineer / 材料工程师','上海','大专以上学历','3 years at least','<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong> <br />• Evaluate, develop, and facilitate implementation of new and alternate source materials into current and new production compounds.<br />• Facilitate implementation of current and new rubber compound formulations by working with the production facilities in optimizing their mixing, extrusion and calendaring processes. <br />• Work with the production facilities in their evaluation and approval of new and alternate source materials.<br />• Track the performance existing suppliers and monitor the quality, consistency and process capability of the raw materials used in current and new production compounds.<br />• Initiate, analyze and summarize laboratory development studies on rubber compounds.<br />• Participate, advise or lead as needed on product development, process improvement and problem solving teams that are by nature global and multi-disciplinary.<br />• Document investigations and plant trials in the form of detailed technical reports, presentations and management updates.<br />• Promote technical relationships with suppliers, universities and other entities to help ensure CTR is aware of and is utilizing material, compounding and processing technologies.<br /><strong>Job Requirements:</strong> <br />• College Diploma (2-3 year) or University Degree (4-year) in Engineering, Chemistry, Mathematics, Technology or Science <br />• Minimum of 3-years of relevant experience in tire rubber compounding and composite technology or in related industry <br />• Multi-lingual: English &amp; Mandarin with sound skills in reading, writing &amp; speaking English<br />• Good communication and technical documentation skills.<br />• Proficiency with design of experiment methods with strong analytical and problem solving skills.<br />• Functional knowledge of tire engineering or manufacturing processes and understanding of quality systems and concepts<br />• Must be detail oriented, self-starting, and must be able to complete projects with minimal supervision.<br />• Proficiency with standard PC applications including: Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Excel, Access and Visio.</p>\r\n<p><strong>工作职责：</strong> <br />1. 评估、开发以及改进现有和新的生产配方中使用的新材料或替代材料。<br />2. 与工厂合作，改进现有和新的生产配方以优化材料合成、挤出和出厂流程。<br />3. 与工厂合作，评估和审批新的和替代的原材料。<br />4. 跟踪和监控现有供应商提供的现行和新的生产配方中使用的新材料或替代材料的质量。<br />5. 启动实验室开发项目，分析和总结所有橡胶合成的实验结果。<br />6. 必要时，参与、建议或领导全球性和综合性的产品开发、工艺改善以及问题解决团队的项目。<br />7. 将所有调查研究和工厂试验的结果形成详细的技术报告、介绍等文件，作为管理文件更新。<br />8. 促进与供应商、大学和其它机构的关系，确保固铂的先进生产工艺<br /><strong>职位要求：</strong> <br />1． 工程、化学、数学、技术或科学类相关专业大专以上学历<br />2． 至少3年以上橡胶配方及合成工艺或相关行业工作经验<br />3． 良好的中英文听说读写能力<br />4． 良好的交流和技术文件撰写能力<br />5． 较强的分析和解决问题的能力，熟悉实验方法设计<br />6． 功能性了解轮胎工程或生产工艺，理解质量系统和概念<br />7． 细致，自律，能独立完成项目<br />8． 计算机应用熟练，包括：Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Excel, Access and Visio.</p>',12,'2012-04-01 10:07:56','2012-04-10 05:00:39'),
	(14,'Pricing specialist','上海','本科','2年以上','<p><strong>Job description</strong> <br />Price database and information maintain<br />*competition model maintenance for price analysis purpose <br />*Competitor price database maintain including competitor price list, promotion update<br />*Wholesale price database maintain and wholesale price <br />*Retail price information collection by telephone interview </p>\r\n<p><strong>Price reporting</strong> <br />*Data analysis and reporting (specific and trends) for Sales and price controlling purposes </p>\r\n<p><strong>Project support</strong> <br />*Price information support of related department</p>\r\n<p><strong>Requirement</strong>Bachelor degree<br />Good command of excel or access, or other data process tool<br />2 years working experience<br />Business knowledge or marketing knowledge is a plus</p>',13,'2012-04-01 10:09:07','2012-04-10 05:02:28'),
	(15,'Customer Service Representative','上海','大专','2-3年','<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<br /> <strong><em>Order fulfillment</em>\r\n</strong> <br />• Quick response to customer orders and inquires <br />• Accurate order allocation and entry into ERP system<br />• Order confirmation and coordination with sales team and customers <br /> <em><strong>Order delivery coordination</strong> </em>• Order releasing tracking to ensure on-time delivery <br />• Goods outbound confirmation with logistic to ensure monthly closing <br /> <em><strong>Sales administration</strong>\r\n</em> <br />• Customer data management <br />• Order related documentation filling and recording <br />• Other administration work to support sales team <br /> General reporting required </p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong>\r\n<br /> College Degree above<br /> 2~3 years of working experience , better in order fulfillment working field ;<br /> Basic knowledge of commercial trade and logistics procedure;<br /> ERP system experience required ( JDE preferred );<br /> Strong interpersonal and communication skills;<br /> Self motivated and self starter, good team player;<br /> Good operation of office soft ware especially in excel.</p>',14,'2012-04-10 03:20:48','2012-04-10 05:04:05'),
	(16,'Consumer Marketing Supervisor ','上海','本科','4年以上','<p><strong>Main Responsibilities</strong>:<br />• Responsible for developing and executing marketing campaign in support of branding and business goals.<br />• Plan and implement key product launch related projects and activities.Plan and implement annual dealer conferenceDevelop effective, efficient process to support key marketing campaign and activities.<br />• Develop strong working relationships with colleagues in product marketing, trade marketing and sales team.<br />• Communicate project status, progress, and challenges with internal team.<br />• Solid experience in event execution/management, PR and agency management Preferred</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>Requirements</strong>:<br />• Strong strategic marketing communication and project management skills.<br />• Rich experience and Decisive execution in campaign and event.<br />• Team working spirit, Coordinating and self management skill.<br />• Be very organized, selfdisciplined, and able to work independently under <br />pressure with tight deadlines.<br />• Euro/US company/brand background, Car or car parts industry background.<br />• At least 4years related working experience, agency experience is preferred.Bachelor degree or above. </p>',15,'2012-04-10 04:03:55','2012-04-10 05:05:19'),
	(17,'HR Supervisor ','上海','本科','5年以上','<p><strong>Report to</strong>：HR Director</p>\r\n<p><strong>Scope of responsibility</strong>This position will be responsible for consolidation of the company china recruitment needs, building recruitment channels for various talents attraction, tracking recruitment progress, support C&amp;B policies and related report etc.</p>\r\n<p>This role will also manage yearly campus recruitment program and technical school cooperation &amp; technical students internship programs.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Key Responsibility</strong>\r\n<br /> Consolidate recruitment needs based upon HC budget &amp; budget development<br /> Develop and maintain different recruitment channels for recruitment<br /> Analyze the performance of current recruitment channels &amp; suppliers and update the channels on a yearly base<br /> Develop new approach to attract talents and improve recruitment efficiency<br /> Monitor &amp; report monthly recruitment status<br /> Take the lead to manage yearly campus recruitment program<br /> Be responsible for new graduates yearly introduction program<br /> Work with each region on technical school students internship program<br /> Analyze employee turnover and propose corresponding actions<br /> Coordinate each hiring managers on JD update<br /> Manage e-recruitment system<br /> Update the positions released on E-Recruitment System<br /> Build a candidate/talent pools through E-Recruitment System<br /> Support C&amp;B policies and related labor market data gathering, be involved in market survey project<br /> Understand salary structure and benefit package<br /> Be responsible for administration of payroll and implementation of C&amp;B related activities in line with company’s policy and local labor law<br /> To implement payroll and income tax issues and prepare related reports</p>\r\n<p><strong>Qualification/Experience&#160; </strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>More than 5 years related working experience<br />&#160;&#160;&#160; &#160; Education Bachelor degree and equivalent<br />&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &#160;Language Good command of oral and written English</p>\r\n<p><strong>Special Requirements</strong> Good planning, organizing, coordinating, control capability<br /> Initiative and good communication<br /> Hard work and strong analysis<br /> Familiar with computer skills<br /> Good interpersonal skill and team player</p>',16,'2012-04-10 04:06:12','2012-04-10 05:08:56');
